Blanco (white), also called plata (silver), is typically naged or aged no longer than 60 days, and therefore has the most distinctive taste of pre agave. Blancos are typically floral and herbal with clean minerality and a peppery bite

Reposado, literally meaning \201crested\201d, refers to the teqila aging from a period of 2 months to 1 year in oak barrels. The aging process is designed to mellow the agave creating a smoother teqila, great for sipping.
